# Keep the Vercel deploy Node-only. These are the repo-root ML/Python artifacts,
# not part of the web build. Every pattern is anchored with a leading slash so it
# ONLY matches the repo root — never frontend/src, frontend/src/data, etc.
# (An unanchored "src/" or "data/" would match those nested dirs and break the build.)
/requirements.txt
/*.ipynb
/.ipynb_checkpoints/
/notebooks/
/models/
/data/
/scripts/
/src/

# Defensive, unanchored: any Python source or manifest ANYWHERE in the tree.
# Vercel's zero-config framework detection keys off files it finds in the upload;
# a single stray .py or requirements.txt is enough to misdetect the project as
# Python even with `framework: "vite"` set. There are no Python files under
# frontend/, so these globs are safe to leave unanchored and stop a future stray
# file (e.g. a new script dropped outside /scripts/) from re-triggering that.
*.py
requirements*.txt
Pipfile
Pipfile.lock
pyproject.toml
setup.py
